  <front>
    <title>Port Control Protocol (PCP) Failure Scenarios</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-boucadair-pcp-failure-03"/>
    <author initials="M." surname="Boucadair" fullname="Mohamed Boucadair"/>
    <author initials="F." surname="Dupont" fullname="Francis Dupont"/>
    <author initials="R." surname="Penno" fullname="Reinaldo Penno"/>
    <date day="25" month="May" year="2012"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>This document identifies and analyzes several PCP failure scenarios.
   A procedure to retrieve the explicit dynamic mapping(s) from the PCP
   Server is proposed.  This procedure relies upon the use of a new PCP
   OpCode and Option: GET/NEXT.</t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
